video_name: Film Theory: Mario is IMMORTAL! (Super Mario Movie)
comment:
I felt that Peach's reason for bringing Mario with her made sense in hindsight.  Toad was literally the only Toad brave enough to go with her, meaning she was pretty much on her own for this adventure otherwise.  Then she meets another human like herself for the first time that wants to go to save his brother.  When Mario demanded to go, she gave him a day to complete a course to prove he wouldn't slow her down. She had already planned to head out to the Kong's island the next day.  So she didn't spend any extra time on him. 

Basically, "Nobody else is going with me tomorrow, and then I meet the first-ever human aside from myself that wants to do it to save his brother. If he can complete this combat course showing he won't slow me down before I leave, he can come along."

comment: the reason mario isn't taking a lost of damage in the DK fight might be because Donkey Kong actually wasn't kidding when he said he let Mario win. He seemed to really enjoy being the center of attention in that fight, and helping win an even bigger one (against bowser) would only make him more popular. When he heard his dad would send the Kong army (and therefore Donkey Kong himself) if mario beat him in a fight, DK might have gone easy on mario so that he could see some real action. It sure didn't seem like there were many fights happening in the mushroom kingdom besides in the arena for DK, and it was pretty clear he liked action.
